value.Title: Germany
value.Description: Federal Republic of Germany, German Democratic Republic, Germany (old), Saarland.

value.Title: Estonia
value.Description:
Independent State from 1918-1940, and part of the Soviet Union after the Second World War until 1991. Became independent again after the division of the Soviet Union.



As this country has only been distinguished in the registers of Statistics Netherlands during its independence (1918-1940 and since 1991), Statistics Netherlands only counts persons born in these periods as belonging to this country of birth.



This country is also counted in the number of the (former) Soviet Union.

value.Title: Kosovo
value.Description:
New country created by separation from Serbia in 2008. 



As this country is only distinguished separately in the registers of Statistics Netherlands since the division, Statistics Netherlands only counts persons born after the division as belonging to this country of birth.



This country has also been counted in the number of (former) Yugoslavia.
